    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - PRESSURE PROTECTION VALVE - REASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the shim, if used, in the upper body. The same number of shims should be used to
                obtain proper pressure adjustment.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position spring, spring cap and diaphragm on upper body.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place lower body over the assembly and force the two body halves together.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn assembly over and install screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Test repaired valve assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
